label.value: voltage-gated calcium channel activity involved in regulation of cytosolic calcium levels

value.value: Regulation of cytosolic calcium ion concentrations via the directed movement of calcium ions across the plasma-membrane into the cytosol via the action of a voltage-gated calcium ion channel.
A polymer consisting of an indefinite number of protein or protein complex subunits that have polymerised to form a fiber-shaped structure.
A component of the cytoskeleton consisting of a homo or heteropolymeric fiber constructed from an indeterminate number of protein subunits.
The directed movement of synaptic vesicles along cytoskeletal fibers such as microfilaments or microtubules within a cell, powered by molecular motors.
The transport of organelles or other particles from one location in the cell to another along actin filaments.
The directed movement of synaptic vesicles along microtubules within a cell, powered by molecular motors.
The directed movement of a vesicle along a cytoskeletal fiber such as a microtubule or and actin filament, mediated by motor proteins.
The directed movement of dense core granules along cytoskeletal fibers, such as microtubules or actin filaments.

label.value: monoatomic ion antiporter activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Any ion antiporter activity, occurring in the presynaptic membrane, that is involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential.

label.value: ATPase coupled ion transmembrane transporter activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Any ATPase coupled ion transmembrane transporter activity, occurring in the presynaptic membrane, that is involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential.
Any (proper) part of the cytosol of a single cell of sufficient size to still be considered cytosol.
The region of the cytosol consisting of all cytosol that is part of the presynapse.
The region of the cytosol consisting of all cytosol that is part of the postsynapse.

The secretion of molecules (e.g. neuropeptides and neuromodulators such as serotonin and dopamine) contained within a membrane-bounced dense in response to increased presynaptic cytosolic calcium levels.

The series of molecular signals that conveys information from the presynapse to the nucleus via cytoskeletal transport of a protein from a presynapse to the component to the nucleus where it affects biochemical processes that occur in the nucleus (e.g DNA transcription, mRNA splicing, or DNA/histone modifications).

definition.value: This class does not cover the cellular machinery (motor proteins, cargo-recognition proteins) that transports the signaling protein along the cytoskeleton towards the nucleus. For these cases, annotate to the appropriate transport/trafficking term.

value.value: The series of molecular signals that conveys information from the postsynapse to the nucleus via cytoskeletal transport of a protein from a postsynapse to the component to the nucleus where it affects biochemical processes that occur in the nucleus (e.g DNA transcription, mRNA splicing, or DNA/histone modifications).

Combining with a neurotransmitter and transmitting the signal across the membrane by activating an associated G-protein; promotes the exchange of GDP for GTP on the alpha subunit of a heterotrimeric G-protein complex.

label.value: neurotransmitter receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: Neurotransmitter receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane that is involved in regulating postsynaptic membrane potential, either directly (ionotropic receptors) or indirectly (e.g. via GPCR activation of an ion channel).

label.value: G protein-coupled receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane that is part of a GPCR signaling pathway that positively regulates ion channel activity in the postsynaptic membrane.

label.value: presynaptic process involved in chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: The pathway leading to secretion of a neurotransmitter from the presynapse as part of synaptic transmission.
The process in which synaptic vesicles fuse to the presynaptic endosome followed by sorting of synaptic vesicle components and budding of new synaptic vesicles.

definition.value: This covers processing of synaptic vesicles trafficked to synapse as well as of endocytosed vesicles as part of recycling. It is there for not part of the synaptic vesicle cycle.

label.value: positive regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium concentration

value.value: Any process that increases the concentration of calcium ions in the presynaptic cytosol.

label.value: calcium ion binding involved in regulation of presynaptic cytosolic calcium ion concentration

value.value: The directed change of presynaptic cytosolic free calcium ion concentration in the cytosol via the reversible binding of calcium ions to calcium-binding proteins in the cytosol thereby modulating the spatial and temporal dynamics of changes in presynaptic cytosolic calcium concentrations.
The extracellular matrix of the perisynaptic space (the extracellular space adjacent to the synapse) and the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling to, from or within a synapse.
Cell-cell signaling in either direction across the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling to or from a synapse, mediated by a peptide.
The secretion of neuropeptides contained within a dense core vesicle by fusion of the granule with the presynaptic membrane, stimulated by a rise in cytosolic calcium ion concentration.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by a peptide ligand crossing the synaptic cleft.
Cell-cell signaling from post to pre-synapse, across the synaptic cleft, mediated by a lipid.
Cell-cell signaling in either direction across the synaptic cleft, mediated by an endocannabinoid ligand.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by a soluble gas ligand crossing the synaptic cleft.
The extracellular region immediately adjacent to to a synapse.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by a trans-synaptic protein complex.

label.value: protein catabolic process, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any protein degradation process, occurring at a presynapse, that regulates synaptic transmission.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by nitric oxide.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse mediated by carbon monoxide.
Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, across the synaptic cleft, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by neuropeptide, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the vesicular release and reception of neuropeptide molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by lipid, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the release and reception of lipid molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by endocannabinoid, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the release and reception of endocannabinoid ligands, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by soluble gas, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the release and reception of gaseous molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by nitric oxide, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the release and reception of nitric oxide molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by carbon monoxide, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, via the release and reception of carbon monoxide molecules, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: trans-synaptic signaling by trans-synaptic complex, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, mediated by transynaptic protein complexes, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: A process that preserves the structural organistation and orientation of a synaptic cellular component such as the synaptic cytoskeleton and molecular scaffolds.

label.value: maintenance of alignment of postsynaptic density and presynaptic active zone

value.value: The process by which alignment between postsynaptic density and presynaptic active zone is maintained.
The attachment of presynaptic membrane to postsynaptic membrane via adhesion molecules that are at least partially embedded in the plasma membrane.

label.value: synaptic membrane adhesion to extracellular matrix

value.value: The binding of a synaptic membrane to the extracellular matrix via adhesion molecules.
